  "prompt": "What do you do if you run out of underwear and money?",
  "response": "Running out of underwear and money can be tricky, but there are still practical steps you can take to manage the situation:\n\n### 1. **Wash and Reuse the Underwear You Have**\n   - If you still have some underwear, even if it\u2019s dirty, wash it by hand using soap and water. Let it dry overnight so you can reuse it the next day.\n\n### 2. **Get Creative with Alternatives**\n   - Use clean clothing like T-shirts, shorts, or towels as temporary underwear until you can get more.\n   - Some people cut up old clothes or use fabric scraps as makeshift underwear.\n\n### 3. **Reach Out for Help**\n   - Ask a trusted friend or family member if they can lend you some underwear or help you out financially.\n   - Check if there are local charities, shelters, or community organizations that provide clothing assistance.\n\n### 4. **Prioritize Purchasing Underwear**\n   - If you can scrape together a small amount of money, prioritize buying a few pairs of affordable underwear from a discount store or thrift shop.\n\n### 5. **Look for Free or Donated Clothing**\n   - Some organizations, like Goodwill, Salvation Army, or local churches, offer free or low-cost clothing, including underwear.\n\n### 6. **Plan Ahead for the Future**\n   - Once you\u2019re back on your feet, consider buying extra pairs of underwear during sales or setting aside a small emergency fund for essentials.\n\n### 7. **Stay Positive**\n   - Remember, this is a temporary situation, and it\u2019s okay to ask for help when you need it. Everyone experiences tough times, and there\u2019s no shame in doing what you need to get by.\n\nHang in there\u2014solutions are always available, even in tough situations!",
